# Local Cloudflare API tokens for infra-setup scripts (gitignored copy: .env.cloudflare).
# Copy: cp .env.cloudflare.example .env.cloudflare
# Fill values locally — never commit .env.cloudflare or paste tokens into chat.
# Scripts load this via infra-setup/lib/common.sh (role-specific key, then fallback).

# Optional account override (public default is already in docs/provision.md)
# CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=

# Zone DNS Edit (squadme.app) + Workers Scripts Edit — apex attach
# npm run attach:production:hostname
# CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN_DNS=

# Access: Apps and Policies Edit (+ Organizations / Service Tokens as needed)
# npm run provision:access:dev | provision:access:smoke:dev
# CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN_ACCESS=

# Fallback for the keys above; also used by npm run ci:wire-secrets (CI deploy token)
# Keep scopes separate when possible (Access ≠ DNS ≠ CI).
# CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=

# Optional: Access service-token pair for local / GHA smoke (from provision:access:smoke:dev)
# CF_ACCESS_CLIENT_ID=
# CF_ACCESS_CLIENT_SECRET=
